{
  "doc_id": "18880",
  "text": "Foxp3 YFP-Cre [CITATION_1] , Foxp3 eGFP-CreERT2 [CITATION_2] , Tcra FL [CITATION_3] , Foxp3 KO [CITATION_4] , G113Tg [CITATION_5] ), Fox-p3 DTReGFP [CITATION_6] , and Tcra FL/Vα14i-StopF [CITATION_7] mice have been previously described. CD45.1 and Tcrb −/− Tcrd −/− mice were purchased from The Jackson Laboratory. Mice were sex and age matched in all experiments, with the exception of experiments involving only female G113TgFoxp3 CreERT2/YFP-Cre Tcra FL/FL mice. Generation and treatments of mice were performed under protocol 08-10-023 approved by the Sloan Kettering Institute Institutional Animal Care and Use Committee. All mouse strains were maintained in the Sloan Kettering Institute animal facility in specific pathogen-free conditions in accordance with institutional guidelines.",
